A flavorful dish on its own but superb for plating a grilled salmon filet. I made the following modifications/additions: olive oil instead of vegetable, jamaica curry powder (strong ginger notes), Szego paprika, a vegetable bouillon cube, cherry tomatoes, and finely chopped parsely. I simmered the curry for one hour on low heat to develop the flavor. Then I ladled the curry onto soup plates and placed a grilled salmon fillet on top. Mm.

